-! can be appended to a method name to show that it is destructive
  it is part of the method name and part of ruby syntax
-it is also known as the 'bang operator' and can be prepended to an object
  to reverse or negate it's boolean value
  -? can be appended to a method name to show that it returns a boolean
    it is part of the method name and part of ruby syntax

1. What is != and where should you use it?
  != means 'does not equal', to be used for comparison

2. put ! before something, like !user_name
  negates the object's boolean value

3. put ! after something, like words.uniq!
  used to demonstrate that the method is destructive and mutates the caller

4. put ? before something
  ? : is the ternary operator for if/else

5. put ? after something
  used in method name to demonstrate that the method will return a boolean

6. put !! before something, like !!user_name
 used to turn something into it's boolean equivalent
